name: iron-chelate-transporting ATPase
classes: Acting on acid anhydrides to catalyse transmembrane movement of substances
reaction: ATP + H2O + iron chelateout = ADP + phosphate + iron chelatein [RN:R00086]
comment: ABC-type (ATP-binding cassette-type) ATPase, characterized by the presence of two similar ATP-binding domains. Does not undergo phosphorylation during the transport process. A bacterial enzyme that imports Fe-enterobactin, Fe-dicitrate, Fe-hydroxamate and other siderophores.

orthologs.K02013: iron complex transport system ATP-binding protein
